    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:250
    old "The man has to be older than forty. He wears an elegant blue-green linen tunic, but no armor. His skin is yellowish, like seaweed seen through a sunbeam. His long gray hair is tied in a ponytail, and his beard is trimmed to half a finger of length. A few large cysts make him look sickly, but his powerful, truculent voice adds to him strength and confidence. \n\n“Cheers, stranger, you’ve reached {color=#f6d6bd}Gale Rocks{/color}, you did,” he observes your mount, then looks at the path behind you. “I see no caravan from here, are they coming?” He suddenly meets your eyes, and his tone gets even harsher. “Or are you here to idle about?” "
