    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:1256
    old "“Once a year, we make something out of apples and cherries,” you hear from a farmer, “but when we drink anything brought here from the South, it’s a great hit to our coin chest. We’d rather buy hemp from {color=#f6d6bd}Old Págos{/color}, at least it won’t leak out of a cask or a pot.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:1282
    old "Carrying heavy weights around is done mostly by the young people. They transport tools, buckets of water, baskets of meals and ingredients, wagons of firewood, and barrels of raw or dressed fish. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:1295
    old "It turns out that the villagers hunt only on the most desperate days, usually to catch creatures that may be of use later on, not for their meat. “Unless you count the fishers,” says one of the carriers. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:1309
    old "You learn that the majority of the local seafolk work as fishers since they can hold their breath for longer than most of their neighbors. The locals have many different skin tones, signs of dozens of families who moved to this area across the centuries, but you recognize the coastal blood in most of them - the wavy hair, long limbs, small ears, and almost complete lack of beards. Still, if they were just some of the many faces you would spot in the city square, you wouldn’t even notice these features. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:1328
    old "There’s only one animal pen in the entire village, and not a very large one. In front of the thatched shed you find a few ibexes, boars, and a large group of pheasants, whose pinioned or clipped wings make it impossible for them to cross the wall, though not the fence - some of them have already left the enclosure, and the locals let them wander about.[custom1] "
    new ""

    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:1346
    old "You learn that the locals craft mostly in winters, and only work on the things they need for themselves. The only year-long artisans are the carpenters and coopers, but even they produce almost exclusively barrels. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:1360
    old "Since the village has no forest garden and almost no foragers, there is no local tradition of potion making. You’re told to ask {color=#f6d6bd}Foggy{/color} about her own alchemy set, which she uses to brew ciders and distill hard drinks. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:1376
    old "Your search for an inn is futile, and the locals are quite proud that they have no place “to waste their days with mugs and dice.” They explain that if any caravan needs to stay the night, there’s always enough space to empty one of the caves. “If you need a room to spend the night,” you’re told, “{color=#f6d6bd}Fulvia{/color} may have something.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:1394
    old "There are no obvious people you could ask about such a service, as everyone seems to be busy with their tasks. You finally head toward a tidy woman who’s standing by herself, and she looks at you with bewilderment. “Ehm, no soul here needs to do such things to earn their soup, and no one wants to. You’d faster find a betrothed here than a shag. We don’t sleep with newcomers, who knows what illnesses they bring,” to illustrate her words, she points at your crotch. \n\nYou start to walk away, but she suddenly calls after you. “You may look for someone at {color=#f6d6bd}Creeks{/color}, [custom1]. It’s the village of hunters, east of {color=#f6d6bd}Foggy’s{/color}.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:1409
    old "You’ve learned that the locals can’t rely on the herbs that grow in the rocky hills and leas. “When we {i}have to{/i}, we seek help from {color=#f6d6bd}Thyrsus{/color}, the herbalist of {color=#f6d6bd}White Marshes{/color}. He cares for the peat fields.” You try to learn more about him, but everyone you ask admits to not knowing him all that well. “He just listens to what we need, says his price, and makes us go, he does.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:1429
    old "The villagers react with distrustful scowls, but after just a few minutes you find an elder wearing a winged hourglass. When he hears your question, he fearfully grasps the pendant and speaks with closed eyes. “So you’re looking for them, roadwarden! May The Wright bless you!” He looks at you again, with a shadow of a smile on the corner of his lips. “Be brave, and crush them in {color=#f6d6bd}White Marshes{/color}, the village in the west, hidden among the wetlands like them saurians in water!” \n\nYou ask him to tell you anything more, but his memory finds little knowledge to back up his zeal. “They are dark wizards who build their army to crush us all, yet no one listens to my calls, only The Good One, who had sent you to me!” He flashes you a wide, toothless smile. “Show them your strength, and never hide your axe!” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:1443
    old "You ask a few other souls, but none of them has anything new to tell you. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:1459
    old "You ask about any unusual creatures that may present a threat to the locals, and you learn that for a few good years now everything seems under control, aside from harpies. “They take no bait, no food. All them beasts do nothing but fly and seek weaklings to catch. We tried to tame them with fish, but they never learn, dumber than a bat they are.” \n\nOnce their tale ends, an older worker clears his throat. “Ehm... I don’t feel well with the walking shells from the tunnel, in the south,” he doesn’t look at you, as if he’s speaking against his will. “I know not where they came from, but I once shot at them with a bow. It just... The arrow, right? {color=#f6d6bd}Florus{/color}, the fletcher, makes good ones... Flew through the bones. No flesh to stop it. I ran for help, but the awoken was gone before we came back.” \n\nHis friend pats his shoulder. “Next time aim for the head, that’s all.” "
    new ""

    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:1474
    old "You ask about any new threats approaching the walls, but so far the wilderness has been quiet. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:1487
    old "There’s quite a group of lumberjacks working in the village, more than ten people strong, but the woods are far away, and the coopers and carpenters take a good few days to process the entire supply. “In better years, we used to buy timber from other villages. Now, finding them on our own takes so much time it’s hardly worth the effort.” \n\nMost of the time, the crew seeks weak and dying trees, using them to fuel the fires of smokers and salters. "
    new ""

    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:1487
    old "I look for a worker who is a bit older, and ask them about the abandoned camp I’ve heard about."
    new ""

    # game/areas/galerocks01structure.rpy:1495
    old "You’re told to speak with a limping farmer in his sixties. Hearing your question, he spares you a grin. “That’s where I worked, right! And where I lost half of my foot,” he laughs briefly and hits his left boot with a hoe, but since it’s closed, it doesn’t reveal any wounds. “We spent a few springs and summers there, we did, many years ago, but once the cats moved in during winter, we had to quit. It was a cute spot, with carpets of flowers, and so many frogs...” \n\nWhen you ask him for some directions, he smiles at the clouds. “We used to go from here to the crossroads, where {color=#f6d6bd}Foggy{/color} now has her tavern, then farther south, to the watchtower, and then west, through the shortcut. That’s where you’ll find the cairn, in the heart of the woods, and a path north from there, to the camp.” "
